      <hedline>
        <hl1>PARTS MAKERS HIT</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By John Tagliabue</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Tagliabue, John</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Michelin tire company and Valeo SA report disappointing results as result of slowdown in automobile market; Michelin says first-half operating income fell 9.4 percent, to 540 million euros, or $469 million; Valeo says it will not meet projected full-year operating profit of 7 percent of revenue (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Pinched by a slowdown in automobile markets, the Michelin tire company and Valeo S.A., reported disappointing results. Michelin said first-half operating income fell 9.4 percent, to 540 million euros, or $469 million. Valeo said it would not meet a projected full-year operating profit of 7 percent of revenue.</p>
        <p>John Tagliabue (NYT)</p>
      </block>
